 Port Eliabeth - The Mandela Bay Development Agency (MBDA) on Thursday advised Port Elizabeth motorists of possible traffic disruptions in the Baakens Valley area. "Please be advised that the Baakens pedestrian bridge contractor got a permit to transport the steel bridge over the next three days, 04, 05, and 08 July 2019, between 9.00am to 15.00pm, from Uitenhage to Baakens Valley," the MBDA said. "The steel bridge will take up about 3 hours to transport to site. "The plan is to leave Uitenhage each day at 9.00am and arrive at about 12.00pm on those three days. We will keep you updated if there are any changes to the plan." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 